        <h1>Refurbishment of Great Portland Street station</h1>
        <div class="content-page-press-release">
        15 September 2005
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
<div class="main-and-aside r">
    <div class="main" role="main">

    <div class="article-teaser">
        Refurbishment work is presently underway to improve Great Portland Street station as part of Transport for London's (TfL) five-year, &pound;10bn investment programme.
        
    </div>



 <div class="on-this-page">
<div class="pullquote right">
                        <p>
                            Passengers are advised to use nearby stations or buses after 2200
                            
                        </p>
                    </div>
                
            
            
            <p>While ongoing refurbishment work takes place, trains will not stop at Great Portland Street station from 2200 until close of service each night from 26 September until 4 March 2006, except on 24, 26 and 31 December and 1 January 2006.</p>
<p>The ticket office will remain open and passenger-operated ticket machines will be available after 2200 during this time for the purchase of Travelcards and Oyster card top-ups.</p>
<p>The refurbishment works being undertaken by Metronet Rail SSL will include improved CCTV coverage, installation of customer help points, an enhanced public address system and complete station redecoration.</p>
<p>After 2200 from 26 September, customers are advised to use Regent's Park station on the Bakerloo line, Warren Street on the Victoria line or London buses to/from Baker Street or Euston Square.</p>
<hr>

<p>For 24-hour information on public transport in London, please call: 020 7222 1234.<br><br>TfL's Realtime pages display live travel information on London's public transport network: <a href="http://www.tfl.gov.uk/realtime">www.tfl.gov.uk/realtime</a> </p>
<p>Journey Planner checks the transport network's status before providing results. The best available route is shown automatically: <a href="http://www.tfl.gov.uk/journeyplanner">www.tfl.gov.uk/journeyplanner</a> </p>
<p>Travel alerts via SMS and email can be set up at: <a href="http://www.tfl.gov.uk/alerts">www.tfl.gov.uk/alerts</a></p>

     

        
        
        
